transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Jimmy.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Hey Jimmy, I want to cancel my prescription, please.

Speaker 2: Okay, let me see if I can help you with that.

Speaker 1: I'll pull up your information with your phone number.

Speaker 2: Help me one second.

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: Am I speaking to Larry?

Speaker 1: You are.

Speaker 2: Okay, Larry, let me see if I—

Speaker 1: Let's see what I see for you.

Speaker 2: All right, Larry, I currently see

Speaker 1: that you're getting the Viagra, the 50 milligrams.

Speaker 2: I suspect that you're getting 10 every—

Speaker 1: It looks like that they postponed it for you

Speaker 2: to like every six months.

Speaker 1: Is there any particular reason why you want to—

Speaker 2: Is there any reason why you want to cancel,

Speaker 1: if you don't mind me asking?

Speaker 2: Just not doing it for me and I don't like the side effects.

Speaker 1: Oh, you know, Larry, I'm looking at your prescription here

Speaker 2: and I see you're getting the 50 milligrams of the Viagra.

Speaker 1: Can I make a suggestion for you?

Speaker 2: Instead of just canceling altogether,

Speaker 1: because what I want to do—

Speaker 2: All right, because I want to try to give you

Speaker 1: the upgraded Viagra that doesn't have

Speaker 2: those same side effects.

Speaker 1: That's what I was trying to do.

Speaker 2: No, thank you.

Speaker 1: Because I see you're only currently getting

Speaker 2: the generic Viagra and that's probably

Speaker 1: why you're having those side effects.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I appreciate it, but no thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, not a problem.

Speaker 2: We're going to take care of that for you.

Speaker 1: As I mentioned again, I do see you was postponed

Speaker 2: for six months, but give me one second—

Speaker 1: and we'll go ahead and cancel your subscription.

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: And can you send me an email to that effect?

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, one should automatically generate,

Speaker 1: but like I said again,

Speaker 2: it's definitely getting canceled right now.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, very good.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye.
